    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nOn Windows, `fnamemodify(..., ':h')` does not preserve UNC share roots such as `//foo/C$`.\n\n`C$` is a Windows administrative share for the root of the `C:` drive, so `//foo/C$` should be treated as the UNC root instead of being split like an ordinary path (`//foo/C$` erroneously goes to `//foo` on nightly).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vim\necho fnamemodify('//foo/C$', ':h')\necho fnamemodify('//foo/C$/', ':h')\necho fnamemodify('//foo/C$/bar', ':h')\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```text\n//foo/C$\n//foo/C$\n//foo/C$\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nLatest master/nightly.\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot checked.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nnixos\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghosty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from repo / nightly",
